{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a managed durable execution platform that works with any HTTP server. Instead of running a separate cluster (as Temporal requires), Inngest calls your app's API endpoint on each step and persists the step output itself \u2014 making it trivially deployable on serverless runtimes like Vercel, Netlify, AWS Lambda, and Railway."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Inngest architecture: your app exposes /api/inngest, Inngest Cloud calls it per step and stores step output in its journal"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Inngest Works"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest's model is the inverse of Temporal's polling model:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Your app", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " registers durable functions at a single HTTP endpoint ("}, {"type": "text", "text": "POST /api/inngest", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") using the SDK."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " calls that endpoint once per step, passing the current step's state. Your code runs the step, returns the result, and the HTTP response ends."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " persists the step output in its journal. If a step fails, it retries by calling the endpoint again with the same state."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "On retry", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", completed steps return their cached results instantly \u2014 the same replay guarantee as Temporal, but over HTTP."}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No persistent process is needed. A serverless function that times out at 60 seconds can run a workflow with 100 steps \u2014 each step is a separate invocation. Inngest handles the state between invocations."}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Installation and Setup"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pip install inngest\n\n# Local dev server (simulates Inngest Cloud)\nnpx inngest-cli@latest dev\n\n# Your app registers functions at http://localhost:8000/api/inngest\n# The dev server UI is at http://localhost:8288\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Defining a Durable Function"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.run()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to create checkpointed steps. Each step name must be unique within a function. Completed steps are memoized \u2014 retries skip them."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import inngest\nimport anthropic\n\n# Create the Inngest client\nclient = inngest.Inngest(app_id=\"my-ai-app\")\n\n# Define a durable function triggered by an event\n@client.create_function(\n    fn_id=\"research-agent\",\n    trigger=inngest.TriggerEvent(event=\"agent/research.requested\"),\n    retries=3,\n)\nasync def research_agent(ctx: inngest.Context, step: inngest.Step) -> str:\n    topic: str = ctx.event.data[\"topic\"]\n\n    # step.run() checkpoints the result \u2014 if the function retries, this\n    # step is skipped and the cached result is returned immediately.\n    outline = await step.run(\n        \"generate-outline\",\n        lambda: generate_outline_activity(topic),\n    )\n\n    # Each section is a separate checkpointed step\n    sections = []\n    for i, section_title in enumerate(outline.split(\"\\n\")[:5]):\n        content = await step.run(\n            f\"generate-section-{i}\",\n            lambda t=section_title, idx=i: generate_section_activity(t, idx),\n        )\n        sections.append(content)\n\n    return \"\\n\\n\".join(sections)\n\n\nasync def generate_outline_activity(topic: str) -> str:\n    llm = anthropic.Anthropic()\n    return llm.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-5\",\n        max_tokens=500,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Create a 5-section outline for: {topic}\"}],\n    ).content[0].text\n\n\nasync def generate_section_activity(title: str, index: int) -> str:\n    llm = anthropic.Anthropic()\n    return llm.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=300,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Write section {index+1}: {title}\"}],\n    ).content[0].text\n"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "step.run() must be a lambda or callable:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " the callable is only invoked if the step has not yet completed. Inngest passes the step ID ("}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"generate-outline\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") to look up the cached result."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step IDs must be unique and stable:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " changing a step ID invalidates the checkpoint for that step. Use descriptive, version-stable names like "}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"generate-section-0\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " rather than indices derived from runtime data."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Serving Functions (FastAPI)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from fastapi import FastAPI\nimport inngest.fast_api\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\n# Register all Inngest functions with FastAPI in one call\ninngest.fast_api.serve(\n    app,\n    client,\n    [research_agent, summarise_document, send_weekly_report],\n)\n\n# Inngest Cloud calls POST /api/inngest on each step.\n# Local dev: npx inngest-cli@latest dev --no-discovery\n#            then register your app at http://localhost:8288\n"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest also provides middleware for "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Django", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Flask", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", and raw ASGI/WSGI apps. The serve call registers all functions and mounts the "}, {"type": "text", "text": "/api/inngest", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " endpoint."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sending Events"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trigger Inngest functions by sending events with "}, {"type": "text", "text": "client.send()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Events are named strings with arbitrary JSON data."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import asyncio\nimport inngest\n\nclient = inngest.Inngest(app_id=\"my-ai-app\")\n\nasync def trigger_research(topic: str):\n    # Send an event to trigger the research_agent function\n    ids = await client.send(\n        inngest.Event(\n            name=\"agent/research.requested\",\n            data={\"topic\": topic},\n        )\n    )\n    print(f\"Event sent: {ids}\")\n\nasyncio.run(trigger_research(\"Transformer architecture for beginners\"))\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Durable Sleep and Human-in-the-Loop"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.sleep()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for durable pauses (no process held open) and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.wait_for_event()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to pause until a named event arrives \u2014 implementing human-approval flows."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "@client.create_function(\n    fn_id=\"document-review-pipeline\",\n    trigger=inngest.TriggerEvent(event=\"doc/review.started\"),\n    retries=2,\n)\nasync def document_review(ctx: inngest.Context, step: inngest.Step) -> dict:\n    doc_id: str = ctx.event.data[\"doc_id\"]\n\n    # 1. Generate AI summary\n    summary = await step.run(\n        \"summarise\",\n        lambda: summarise_document(doc_id),\n    )\n\n    # 2. Sleep for 24 hours (no process held open \u2014 Inngest resumes us)\n    await step.sleep(\"wait-for-business-hours\", \"24h\")\n\n    # 3. Wait for a human-approval event (up to 7 days)\n    approval_event = await step.wait_for_event(\n        \"wait-for-approval\",\n        event=\"doc/review.approved\",\n        match=\"data.doc_id\",        # only match events where data.doc_id == ctx.event.data.doc_id\n        timeout=\"7d\",\n    )\n\n    if approval_event is None:\n        # Timeout \u2014 no approval received in 7 days\n        return {\"status\": \"expired\", \"doc_id\": doc_id}\n\n    # 4. Send the approved document onward\n    await step.send_event(\n        \"trigger-publish\",\n        inngest.Event(\n            name=\"doc/publish.requested\",\n            data={\"doc_id\": doc_id, \"summary\": summary},\n        ),\n    )\n    return {\"status\": \"approved\", \"doc_id\": doc_id}\n"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "step.sleep() duration:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " accepts strings like "}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"1h\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"30m\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"7d\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". The underlying HTTP invocation ends immediately; Inngest resumes your function at the specified time."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "step.wait_for_event() match:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " the "}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"data.doc_id\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " match ensures only events where "}, {"type": "text", "text": "data.doc_id == ctx.event.data[\"doc_id\"]", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " resume this specific function run. Without a match, any event of that name would resume all waiting runs."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Timeout:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " if "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.wait_for_event()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " times out, it returns "}, {"type": "text", "text": "None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Always check for "}, {"type": "text", "text": "None", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " and handle the expired case explicitly."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fan-Out and Parallel Execution"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Send multiple events from "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.send_event()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to fan out work across independent function runs. Each child function has its own durable state and retry budget."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "@client.create_function(\n    fn_id=\"batch-summariser\",\n    trigger=inngest.TriggerEvent(event=\"batch/summarise.requested\"),\n)\nasync def batch_summariser(ctx: inngest.Context, step: inngest.Step) -> list:\n    doc_ids: list[str] = ctx.event.data[\"doc_ids\"]\n\n    # Fan out \u2014 send one event per document; each triggers summarise_one\n    await step.send_event(\n        \"fan-out-docs\",\n        [inngest.Event(name=\"doc/summarise.one\", data={\"doc_id\": did}) for did in doc_ids],\n    )\n    # batch_summariser returns immediately; summarise_one functions run independently\n    return {\"queued\": len(doc_ids)}\n\n\n@client.create_function(\n    fn_id=\"summarise-one\",\n    trigger=inngest.TriggerEvent(event=\"doc/summarise.one\"),\n    concurrency=inngest.Concurrency(limit=5),  # max 5 parallel executions\n)\nasync def summarise_one(ctx: inngest.Context, step: inngest.Step) -> str:\n    doc_id = ctx.event.data[\"doc_id\"]\n    return await step.run(\"summarise\", lambda: summarise_document(doc_id))\n"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The parent function ("}, {"type": "text", "text": "batch_summariser", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") does not wait for child functions to complete \u2014 it fans out and returns. Use a separate aggregation function triggered by a "}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"batch/complete\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " event if you need a barrier after all children finish."}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cron Scheduling"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Set "}, {"type": "text", "text": "trigger=inngest.TriggerCron(cron=...)", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for time-based execution. Inngest handles the scheduling \u2014 no external cron service needed."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "@client.create_function(\n    fn_id=\"weekly-report\",\n    trigger=inngest.TriggerCron(cron=\"0 9 * * 1\"),   # every Monday 09:00 UTC\n    retries=2,\n)\nasync def weekly_report(ctx: inngest.Context, step: inngest.Step) -> str:\n    data = await step.run(\"fetch-metrics\", fetch_weekly_metrics)\n    report = await step.run(\"generate-report\", lambda: generate_report(data))\n    await step.run(\"send-email\", lambda: send_email_report(report))\n    return \"done\"\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Throttle and Concurrency"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest provides first-class controls to prevent hammering rate-limited APIs like OpenAI or Anthropic."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Rate-limit LLM calls across all concurrent function runs\n@client.create_function(\n    fn_id=\"summarise-document\",\n    trigger=inngest.TriggerEvent(event=\"doc/summarise.one\"),\n    # At most 10 executions of this function per minute across all instances\n    throttle=inngest.Throttle(count=10, period=\"1m\"),\n    # At most 3 concurrent executions at any time\n    concurrency=inngest.Concurrency(limit=3),\n    retries=3,\n)\nasync def summarise_document_fn(ctx: inngest.Context, step: inngest.Step) -> str:\n    doc_id = ctx.event.data[\"doc_id\"]\n    return await step.run(\"summarise\", lambda: summarise_document(doc_id))\n"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Control"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use case"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "throttle"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Max N executions per time period globally"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LLM API rate limits (RPM)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "concurrency"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Max N simultaneous executions at any moment"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "DB connection pool limits"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "retries"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Max retry attempts on failure"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transient API errors"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "debounce"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Delay + deduplicate rapid-fire events"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "User-typing / search-as-you-type"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest vs Temporal"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Temporal"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Execution model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "HTTP push (Inngest calls your app)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Worker polling (worker calls Temporal)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Infrastructure"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Managed SaaS (or self-host with Docker)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Self-hosted cluster or Temporal Cloud"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Serverless support"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Native (Vercel, Lambda, Cloudflare Workers)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Requires persistent process"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Language support"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TypeScript (primary), Python, Go"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python, Java, Go, TypeScript, .NET"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step granularity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "step.run() / step.sleep() / step.wait_for_event()"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "workflow.execute_activity() / sleep / signal"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fan-out"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "step.send_event() \u2192 independent runs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "child workflows / signal fan-out"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Replay on code change"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stable step IDs required"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "workflow.get_version() required"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dev experience"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "npx inngest-cli dev (local UI)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "docker + temporalite / Temporal CLI"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pricing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Per step execution (generous free tier)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Temporal Cloud: per action; self-hosted: infra cost"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Pitfalls"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Changing step IDs:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " renaming "}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"generate-outline\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to "}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"create-outline\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " invalidates the checkpoint. In-flight runs will re-execute that step. Only change step IDs deliberately, and only when the underlying logic has also changed."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Non-serialisable step output:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " step return values are serialised to JSON by Inngest. Return plain Python dicts, lists, strings, and numbers from "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.run()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " callbacks \u2014 not Pydantic models, datetime objects, or custom classes without "}, {"type": "text", "text": "dict()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " conversion."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lambda late binding:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " in Python loops, "}, {"type": "text", "text": "lambda: fn(i)", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " captures "}, {"type": "text", "text": "i", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " by reference, so all iterations pass the last value of "}, {"type": "text", "text": "i", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "lambda v=i: fn(v)", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " or a closure to capture the current value."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Missing match in wait_for_event:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " without a "}, {"type": "text", "text": "match", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " parameter, "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.wait_for_event()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " resumes on any event with the given name \u2014 including events meant for other workflow runs. Always scope the match to a document/user/session ID."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large step payloads:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " Inngest serialises and stores every step output. Steps that return megabytes of text (large document extracts) hit Inngest's payload size limit. Store large blobs in S3 or a database and return only the reference ID from the step."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Summary"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " delivers durable execution over HTTP \u2014 your app exposes one endpoint; Inngest calls it per step and persists results in its journal."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.run()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for checkpointed steps, "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.sleep()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for durable pauses, and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.wait_for_event()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for human-in-the-loop approval flows."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fan out with "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.send_event()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to spawn independent parallel child runs; control throughput with "}, {"type": "text", "text": "throttle", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "concurrency", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest runs natively on serverless \u2014 no persistent process required, making it the lowest-friction choice for apps already deployed on Vercel, Lambda, or Railway."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stable step IDs are critical: changing an ID invalidates the checkpoint and forces the step to re-run. Keep step names descriptive and version-stable."}]}]}]}]}}